article.headline: North Texas 70, Lamar 66
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Leonard Hopkins scored 22 points to lead North Texas to a 70-66 win over Lamar on Saturday night. Hopkins was 6-of-16 from the field and hit eight of his nine free throws for the Mean Green (3-1). North Texas, which led throughout the second half, also got 14 points from Ty Thomas. Michael Jones, who was 5-of-9 from the field, scored 12. Isaac Hines grabbed nine rebounds for North Texas. Thomas Fairley led Lamar (1-1) with 23 points and 16 rebounds. Raymond Anthony added 16 points. Both teams struggled from the field, shooting close to 40 percent. North Texas led by only one at the half, then hit 11 of 13 second-half free throws. The Cardinals could hit only five of its 14 shots from the free-throw line during the second half.
